The paper deals with the problem of creating orthogonal drawings of graphs, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The problem involves constraints on the number of bends per edge, which is a combinatorial aspect (cs.DM) of the problem. The paper also discusses the computational complexity of the problem, which is a topic in theoretical computer science (cs.CC). The use of flow networks in the FPT-algorithm suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the problem of drawing planar graphs with constraints on the number of bends is a classic topic in graph theory (cs.GT).
